title: ESPN: Cowboys to start Cassel after bye week
text:
ESPN: Cowboys to start Cassel after bye week Replaces Brandon Weeden at quarterback Posted: 8:16 AM, October 14, 2015 Updated: 8:16 AM, October 14, 2015 Dallas Cowboys' Matt Cassel (16) throws before an NFL football game against the New England Patriots, Sunday, Oct. 11, 2015, in Arlington, Texas. (AP Photo/Brandon Wade) More Cowboys Headlines 'Limited' or not, Cowboys' Weeden carrying on as Romo sub 
IRVING, Texas - The Dallas Cowboys are turning to Matt Cassel as their quarterback, according to multiple reports Tuesday. 
Brandon Weeden was told that the Cowboys are going to start Cassel against the New York Giants on Oct. 25 after their bye week. Cassell was acquired in late September from the Buffalo Bills in a trade. 
The Cowboys (2-3) apparently decided to make the change after their loss to the New England Patriots on Sunday. Weeden started three games after Tony Romo went down with a broken collarbone and lost all three, completing 64 of 91 passes for 666 yards with one touchdown and two interceptions. 
Against the Patriots, Weeden passed for a season-low 188 yards and completed 26 of 39 passes with one interception. 
In Weedenâ€™s last 11 starts as an NFL quarterback, his record is 0-11. 
Cowboys coach Jason Garrett said earlier that the team would evaluate the quarterbacks and how to proceed going forward until Romo returns. The broken collarbone will keep Romo out of the lineup until Nov. 22 at the earliest. 
Cassel lost a quarterback competition in Buffalo during the preseason with Tyrod Taylor for the starting job. Copyright 2015 The Associated Press. All rights reserved. This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed.
